    q: "Is my Wolf pizza oven a commercial unit or residential?",
    a: "If the model prefix starts with <b>ICBOGP</b> (or older ICBO/Outdoor Living residential series), it's Wolf <b>residential</b> — this page's scope. If the unit is branded <b>Wolf Range</b> or is specifically a restaurant/commercial-foodservice deck oven or conveyor oven in a commercial kitchen setting, that's Wolf Range Commercial (ITW FEG) and falls under <a href='/commercial/pizza-oven-repair/'>commercial pizza oven repair</a> — different company, different parts. Sub-Zero Group Wolf residential does not manufacture a commercial restaurant pizza oven line. For true restaurant foodservice (Middleby Marshall conveyor, Lincoln Impinger, Bakers Pride deck, Wood Stone hearth, Forno Bravo wood-fired), the commercial page covers those brands."
  },
  {
    q: "What does Wolf pizza oven repair cost in LA?",
    a: "Residential diagnostic $89 waived with repair. Typical Wolf ICBOGP bands: gas ignitor $180–$280; thermocouple / temperature sensor $220–$360; rotisserie accessory motor $240–$380; burner cleaning + dual-flame service $220–$380 (outdoor spider-nest + coastal corrosion common); infrared ceramic element $280–$460 (specialty Madison WI parts); gas valve $280–$480; stainless steel panel / corrosion service $180–$320 (coastal PCH installs); Home Connect WiFi module $180–$260; control board $380–$560. Wolf residential service runs at the luxury tier — specialty Sub-Zero Group parts chain with 3-5 day Madison WI OEM lead typical; certified-technician certification applies. Most Wolf pizza oven calls land $280–$620 parts-and-labor. For matched-suite service across Wolf BBQ + Sub-Zero outdoor refrigerator + Cove outdoor dishwasher single-call, diagnostic fee covers the combined visit."
